<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,751,776]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</emphasis>
Originally described from Forte de Itaipú, Santos, São Paulo State, 
<collectingCountry box="[1152,1224,752,776]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Also collected in Cabo Frio, Rio de Janeiro State, Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[682,750,788,812]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Bahia, unpublished data). Specimens were collected under rocks, associated with ascidians. Rio Grande do Norte represent the northernmost report of this species to date.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,859,884]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Elongated body with ruffled margin; background color wine red with three marginal bands; inner black, middle orange and thinner outer black band. Tentacular eyespots arranged in four dorsal and four ventral clusters. Doubled male reproductive structures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,342,967,992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[350,415,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Color</emphasis>
: Background wine red, darker toward the margins. Three marginal bands present. Internal black band broad, middle orange band surrounded by a black thinner band (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1071,1004,1028]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1056,1071,1004,1028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). The inner black band is visible mostly on bright backgrounds, when in dark background or in the field this band appears merged with the dorsal coloration as if it was a denser pigmentation near the margins. All bands interrupted in the zone between tentacles. The black outer band remains conserved after fixation. Cerebral area unpigmented. Ventral color pattern same as dorsally in live worms. After fixation it turns creamy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,259,1185,1208]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Form</emphasis>
: Elongated with rounded ends (
<figureCitation box="[623,692,1184,1208]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[677,692,1184,1208]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Highly ruffled margins (
<figureCitation box="[1013,1083,1184,1208]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1067,1083,1184,1208]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B). After fixation the body distends and becomes rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" box="[197,1286,1256,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,302,1256,1280]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Tentacles</emphasis>
: Margin folds turned backwards that reaches 
<quantity box="[813,902,1256,1280]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
. Tentacular tips whitish (
<figureCitation box="[1183,1250,1256,1280]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1235,1250,1256,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,297,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Eyespots</emphasis>
: Each tentacle bears four eyespots clusters, two dorsal and two ventral. Two are proximal and two distal. Ventro-distal groups bear 
<number box="[491,519,1328,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="50.0">50</number>
eyespots and ventro-proximal clusters around 
<number box="[1055,1083,1328,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="35.0">35</number>
eyespots. Dorsal groups could not be counted due to tentacle folding and coloration. Cerebral eyespot cluster in horse-shoe shape and bearing 
<number pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="19.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="13.0">13 – 25</number>
eyespots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,385,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Digestive system</emphasis>
: Pharynx 
<quantity box="[500,566,1436,1460]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
long, numerously but tenuously folded. Mouth opens at 
<quantity box="[1204,1269,1436,1460]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
from the anterior margin. Pharyngeal folds filled with eosinophilous granules that might be remains of the specimen food (synascidians).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,492,1544,1568]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Epidermis and body wall</emphasis>
: Epidermis short ciliated (
<quantity box="[808,930,1544,1568]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.037">0.037 mm</quantity>
) with a strong basal membrane. Rhabdites present and abundant both dorsally and ventrally. Thin muscular layers 
<quantity box="[952,1066,1580,1604]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.014">0.014 mm</quantity>
thick, consisting of longitudinal, circular and diagonal fibers, respectivelly. Loose parenchyma. Sucker voluminous, 
<quantity box="[1084,1169,1616,1640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
distant from the female gonopore and 
<quantity box="[317,405,1652,1676]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
large. Subcutaneous pigmentation can be seen in histological sections. Cutaneous glands numerous on the dorsal surface and also present ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,320,1725,1748]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Gonopores</emphasis>
: Two male and one female gonopores present. Male gonopores 
<quantity box="[1055,1143,1724,1748]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
large and 
<quantity box="[1265,1353,1724,1748]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="7.4">7.4 mm</quantity>
distant from the anterior margin, positioned on each side of the median line of the body (
<figureCitation box="[1085,1154,1760,1784]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1138,1154,1760,1784]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Female gonopore 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
distant from the male gonopore, located in the median body line and 
<quantity box="[973,1073,1796,1820]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
large (
<figureCitation box="[1151,1219,1796,1820]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1203,1219,1796,1820]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,533,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[197,486,1832,1856]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">Male reproductive system</emphasis>
: Ventrally disposed testes. Male system doubled with corresponding vesicles, stylet (
<quantity box="[158,266,1868,1892]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
), and penis papilla. Penis (
<quantity box="[573,678,1868,1892]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.24">0.24 mm</quantity>
) and male atrium directed backwards (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1195,1868,1892]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1179,1195,1868,1892]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Male atrium 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.24">0.24 mm</quantity>
deep. Large seminal vesicle (
<quantity box="[532,636,1904,1928]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.54">0.54 mm</quantity>
) reaches twice the copulatory structure size. Seminal ducts are repeatedly expanded forming seminal accessory vesicles that reach 
<number box="[848,897,1940,1964]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="0.61">0.61</number>
x 
<quantity box="[927,1031,1940,1964]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.44">0.44 mm</quantity>
. The main seminal vesicle joins the penis papilla posteriorly through an ejaculatory duct. Prostatic vesicle anteriorly disposed (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1228,1976,2000]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[1214,1228,1976,2000]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D) and 
<number box="[1311,1360,1976,2000]" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" value="0.26">0.26</number>
x 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
large.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis box="[197,510,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Female reproductive system</emphasis>
: Vagina short, 
<quantity box="[677,777,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
long. Female atrium 
<quantity box="[1015,1113,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
deep. Cement pouches (
<quantity metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="0.04">0.04 mm</quantity>
) surrounded by dense masses of cement glands (
<figureCitation box="[748,816,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1358,1381]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1440,301,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudobiceros evelinae. A – B (MNRJ-PLAT 13). A— in vivo, dorsal view; B— in vivo, ventral view. C—E (MNRJ-PLAT 11). C— ventral structures; D— sagittal section with indication of male reproductive structures; E— sagittal section with indication of female reproductive structures. cg: cement gland; cp: cement pouches; ed: ejaculatory duct; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; ut: uteri; vs: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
Fig. 
<number box="[801,816,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Uteri occur dorsally to testes and ventrally to intestine. Uterine duct curved backwards and joining the vagina right under a pharyngeal fold.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212297/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" targetBox="[170,1428,307,1303]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1358,1503]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
