<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1547,1824]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,443,1547,1572]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[451,593,1548,1572]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[451,593,1548,1572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Pseudoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species were acknowledged as remarkably homogeneous internally (
<bibRefCitation author="Newman" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" refString="Newman, L. J. &amp; Cannon, L. R. G. (1996) New genera of pseudocerotid flatworms (Platyhelminthes; Polycladida) from Australian and Papua New Guinean coral reefs. Journal of Natural History, 30 (10), 1425 - 1441." type="journal article" year="1996">
Newman &amp; Cannon 
<number box="[333,393,1584,1608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). After the proposition of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Faubel 1984" authorityName="Faubel" authorityYear="1984" box="[807,1141,1584,1608]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[807,971,1584,1608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Pseudobiceros</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[987,1134,1584,1608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" refString="Faubel, A. (1984) The Polycladida, Turbellaria Proposal and establishment of a new system Part II. The Cotylea. Mitteilungen Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 81, 189 - 259." type="journal article" year="1984">
Faubel 
<number box="[1074,1134,1584,1608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1154,1296,1584,1608]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1154,1296,1584,1608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Pseudoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species that presented two male gonopores were relocated in the new genus. 
<taxonomicName box="[891,1033,1620,1644]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[891,1033,1620,1644]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Pseudoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was restricted to species with only one male system present. 
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[448,608,1656,1680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" refString="Faubel, A. (1984) The Polycladida, Turbellaria Proposal and establishment of a new system Part II. The Cotylea. Mitteilungen Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 81, 189 - 259." type="journal article" year="1984">
Faubel (
<number box="[542,600,1656,1680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
therefore recognized the species described by Marcus as 
<taxonomicName class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="evelinae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Pseudobiceros evelinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our specimens fit the characteristics reported on the original description (tentacular eyespots disposal, color pattern and reproductive structures). There are 
<number box="[746,774,1728,1752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" value="22.0">22</number>
<taxonomicName box="[782,946,1728,1752]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[782,946,1728,1752]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Pseudobiceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species and nine of them present the “even color &amp; distinct marginal bands” color pattern, 
<taxonomicName box="[683,804,1764,1788]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="evelinae">
<emphasis box="[683,804,1764,1788]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">P. evelinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being the only species with red as even color known up to date (
<bibRefCitation author="Newman" box="[241,534,1800,1824]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" refString="Newman, L. J. &amp; Cannon, L. R. G. (1997) Nine new species of Pseudobiceros (Platyhelminthes: Polycladida) from the Indo- Pacific. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 45 (2), 341 - 368." type="journal article" year="1997">
Newman &amp; Cannon 
<number box="[474,534,1800,1824]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
